column18: There are limited hours for applying in person for absentee ballot at county clerk's office: Applicants may apply in person or by authorized messenger at the County Clerk‰Ûªs Office:Wednesday, November 2, 2016 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.Thursday, November 3, 2016 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.Friday, November 4, 2016 8:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.Saturday, November 5, 2016 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m.Monday, November 7, 2016 8:30 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
I couldn't get the BOE to tell me hours, so even though the clerk told  me they were open until 8pm on election day, I'm using the state standard deadline of  11/7 at 3pm.

column18: You can vote when you apply for a ballot or take it with you and return it to the BOE (same building). All ballots MUST be returned to the Board of Elections by the close of the polls at 8PM on November 8th, 2016. We offer Thursday evening and Saturday hours throughout October and November leading up to Election Day.
Anticipate hours changing as election gets closer
